# Clinic Model Structure and Field Mappings

## CRITICAL: Model Uses Nested Document Structure

The [src/models/Clinic.ts](mdc:src/models/Clinic.ts) uses a nested address object, NOT flat MSSQL field names:

### Correct Field Access:
```typescript
clinic.clinicId           // Primary key from MSSQL
clinic.name               // Main clinic identifier (string)
clinic.displayName        // Human-readable name (string)
clinic.address.street     // Street address (nested object)
clinic.address.city       // City (nested object)
clinic.address.province   // Province (nested object)
clinic.address.postalCode // Postal code (nested object)
clinic.isRetainedClinic   // Business rule flag (boolean)
clinic.active             // FHIR active status (boolean)
clinic.status             // Status string (active, historical, inactive)
clinic.services           // Services offered (string array)
clinic.type               // Organization type (string array)
```

### WRONG - Old/incorrect field names (don't exist):
```typescript
clinic.clinicName         // USE clinic.name INSTEAD
clinic.clinicAddress      // USE clinic.address.street INSTEAD
clinic.city               // USE clinic.address.city INSTEAD
clinic.province           // USE clinic.address.province INSTEAD
clinic.postalCode         // USE clinic.address.postalCode INSTEAD
clinic.completeName       // USE clinic.displayName INSTEAD
clinic.getDisplayName()   // USE clinic.displayName INSTEAD (it's a field, not a method)
clinic.telecom            // Not in current model
clinic.contact            // Not in current model
```

## Controllers Must Use Correct Fields

[src/controllers/ClinicController.ts](mdc:src/controllers/ClinicController.ts) accessing clinic properties:

```typescript
// CORRECT
clinic.name
clinic.displayName
clinic.address.street
clinic.address.city
clinic.address.province
clinic.address.postalCode
clinic.isRetainedClinic

// WRONG - These don't exist as flat fields
clinic.clinicName
clinic.clinicAddress
clinic.city              // Must use clinic.address.city
clinic.province          // Must use clinic.address.province
```

## Views Must Use Correct Fields

[src/views/ClinicView.ts](mdc:src/views/ClinicView.ts) formatting clinic data:

```typescript
// CORRECT response format
{
  id: clinic.clinicId,
  name: clinic.name,
  displayName: clinic.displayName,
  address: {
    street: clinic.address.street,
    city: clinic.address.city,
    province: clinic.address.province,
    postalCode: clinic.address.postalCode
  },
  isRetainedClinic: clinic.isRetainedClinic,
  active: clinic.active
}
```

## Property Mapping Summary

| API Response Field | Model Field | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|
| name | name | string | Main clinic name |
| displayName | displayName | string | Human-readable name |
| address.street | address.street | string | Street address |
| address.city | address.city | string | City name |
| address.province | address.province | string | Province/state |
| address.postalCode | address.postalCode | string | Postal code |
| active | active | boolean | FHIR active status |
| isRetainedClinic | isRetainedClinic | boolean | Business rule flag |

## Migration Field Mapping (MSSQL to MongoDB)

| MSSQL Column | MongoDB Field |
|---|---|
| ClinicId | clinicId |
| ClinicName | name |
| CompleteName | displayName |
| ClinicAddress | address.street |
| City | address.city |
| Province | address.province |
| PostalCode | address.postalCode |
| IsRetainedClinic | isRetainedClinic |
